    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I would remove entirely renderFn and unmountFn from the API of this connector.\r\n\r\nStumbling on this idea. Actually if you don't need those functions, it means that there is no need for specialization (as a mean to provide custom behavior). Hence there is no need for a connector, as the pattern is a specialization enabler. This means that this should be implemented as a widget factory, not as a connector. With the new dynamic add / remove API, a widget would even be usable directly in InstantSearch.js.\r\n\r\nActually we have another case like that: the analytics widget.",
    "created_at": "2018-02-08T08:29:29Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2698#issuecomment-364037838",
